28/06/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- A two-day summit of the OECD countries' educational ministers wrapped up on Wednesday (28 June) in the Athens suburb of Lagonissi amid tightened security measures, as Greek students and leftist organisations held parallel protests against a new government bill on higher education. 
On Tuesday, clashes broke out between the protestors and police in downtown Athens. 
Police had to use tear gas to disperse the crowd. 
According to media reports, several demonstrators were injured. 
(Elephtherotypia, Avgi - 28/06/06; ANA, ERT - 27/06/06)
